quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Proclaim (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “I have received the divine revelation that some jinns attentively listened to my recitation, so they said, ‘We have heard a unique Qur’an.’"
  72,2,"‘That guides to the path of goodness, we have therefore accepted faith in it; and we shall never ascribe anyone as a partner to our Lord.’"
  72,3,"‘And that our Lord’s Majesty is Supreme – He has neither chosen a wife nor a child.’"
  72,4,"‘And that the fool among us used to utter false exaggerations against Allah.’"
  72,5,"‘Whereas we thought that men and jinns would never fabricate a lie against Allah!’"
  72,6,"‘And indeed some men among humans used to take the protection of some men among jinns, so it further increased their haughtiness.’"
  72,7,"‘And that they assumed, like you humans assume, that Allah would not send any Noble Messenger.’"
  72,8,"‘And we reached the sky, so we found it strongly guarded and filled with comets.’"
  72,9,"‘And that we sometimes used to sit in some places in the sky, to listen; so whoever now listens finds a fiery comet waiting for him.’"
  72,10,"‘And we do not know whether harm is intended for those on the earth, or whether their Lord intends goodness for them.’"
  72,11,"‘And among us some are virtuous and some are the other type; we are split into several branches.’"
  72,12,"‘And we are certain that we cannot defeat Allah in the earth, nor can we run out of His grasp.’"
  72,13,"‘And that when we heard the guidance, we accepted faith in it; so whoever accepts faith in his Lord, has no fear – neither of any loss nor of any injustice.’"
